A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Criminal Procedure – Verdict of Not Criminally Responsible – Eligibility for
3 Evaluation for Discharge
4 FOR the purpose of establishing that a person committed to the Maryland Department of
5 Health after a verdict of not criminally responsible for murder in the first degree or
6 murder in the second degree is not eligible for discharge for at least a certain period
7 of time after the date the person was committed; and generally relating to persons
8 found not criminally responsible.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
10 Article – Criminal Procedure
11 Section 3–114
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2018 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Criminal Procedure
17 3–114.
18 (a) A committed person may be released under the provisions of this section and
19 §§ 3–115 through 3–122 of this title.
20 (b) (1) [A] EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS
21 SUBSECTION, A committed person is eligible for discharge from commitment only if that
22 person would not be a danger, as a result of a mental disorder or an intellectual disability,
23 to self or to the person or property of others if discharged.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
